GLOBAL CONTEXT — READ BEFORE EVERY TASK:
Project: SampleRoll.com (Next.js + Tailwind + Supabase)
New feature: Beat Visualizer at /visualizer route
CRITICAL ISOLATION RULES:
1. NEVER modify any files in /app/dig/ or components used by the Dig page
2. NEVER modify the existing Supabase user auth tables or RLS policies
3. NEVER modify next.config.js unless ONLY adding a new route/redirect
4. NEVER modify globals.css — create visualizer-specific styles only
5. NEVER modify any existing API routes
6. ALL visualizer code lives in /app/visualizer/ and /components/visualizer/
7. ALL visualizer hooks live in /hooks/visualizer/
8. ALL visualizer utils live in /lib/visualizer/
9. If you need shared UI components, COPY them into /components/visualizer/ — do NOT import
from existing shared components
10. Feature flag: use env var NEXT_PUBLIC_VISUALIZER_ENABLED=true to gate the route
DESIGN SYSTEM:
- Background: #1A1209 (deep brown/black)
- Primary text: #F5E6C8 (cream)
- Accent: #C9A94E (gold)
- Secondary: #8A7A66 (warm gray)
- Headings: Playfair Display (Google Font)
- Body: DM Sans (Google Font)
- All UI is dark-mode only, warm editorial aesthetic
- Buttons: gold outline or filled gold with dark text
- Cards/panels: #231A0E with 1px #3D2E18 border, rounded-lg
TECH CONSTRAINTS:
- Audio: Web Audio API + Tone.js for scheduling/LFOs
- Visuals: WebGL (Three.js or raw) — NO WebGPU yet (fallback concerns)
- Export: WebCodecs API with canvas.captureStream() fallback
- State: Zustand for visualizer state (do not add Redux or other state libs)
- No server-side rendering for the visualizer — it should be a client component
- All rendering happens client-side, zero server compute for visuals
VERIFY AFTER EVERY STEP:
- Run `npm run build` — must pass with zero errors
- Visit /dig — must work exactly as before
- Visit /visualizer — new work should render
- No console errors on either page
